<Requirements version="3" hierarchy="LLR">
  <!-- LLRs refining HL--MAP--1.1 Explore Maze -->
  <Requirement ID="LL--MAP--1.1.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Exploration State Machine</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.1</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--MAP--1.1.4</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL--PLAN--1.1.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL--MAP--1.3.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL--SCHED--1.1.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL--RUN--1.1.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL--RUN--1.2.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL--INIT--1.1.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall implement a top-level mission control state machine with at least the states {IDLE, EXPLORE, RETURN_TO_START, SECOND_RUN, COMPLETED} and deterministic transitions between them, such that:
(1) In the IDLE state, the state machine shall wait for receipt of an INIT_COMPLETED indication from the initialization module and then transition to EXPLORE.
(2) In the EXPLORE state, the state machine shall periodically request frontier targets from the frontier-generation module, request paths to the selected target from the path planner, and command the motion controller to execute the resulting motion primitives until either exploration completion or an exploration timeout event is received.
(3) In the RETURN_TO_START state, the state machine shall invoke the return-to-start service to compute a path to the start cell and shall command the motion controller to execute that path until the start cell is reached or a planning failure is reported.
(4) In the SECOND_RUN state, the state machine shall invoke the second-run planning service to compute the fastest path from the start cell to the goal region, shall command the motion controller to execute that path, and shall wait for receipt of a second-run status (success or failure).
(5) In the COMPLETED state, the state machine shall cease issuing new motion commands and maintain the final second-run status for external reporting.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--MAP--1.1.2">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Exploration Start Condition</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.1</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--SCHED--1.1.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL--INTERF--1.1.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL--INIT--1.1.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall cause the mission control state machine to enter the EXPLORE state automatically when, within the periodic control loop, the initialization module has signaled INIT_COMPLETED and the sensor abstraction layer has provided at least one valid set of ultrasonic and infrared measurements.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--MAP--1.1.3">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Exploration Stop Condition</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--ENV--2.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.5</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--MAP--1.3.6</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL--MAP--1.5.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall terminate the EXPLORE state and initiate RETURN_TO_START when either:
(1) the map completeness condition defined by the grid map module indicates that no cell or inter-cell wall segment remains in the UNKNOWN state, or
(2) the global exploration time limit defined in the time-limit requirement has been reached,
whichever condition is signaled first by the corresponding modules.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--MAP--1.1.4">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Frontier-Based Exploration</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.4</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--MAP--1.3.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL--MAP--1.4.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL--PLAN--1.1.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall implement a frontier-based exploration strategy in the EXPLORE state such that the mission control state machine selects as navigation targets cells that are currently classified as UNKNOWN but are adjacent (in the 4-neighborhood) to at least one FREE cell in the internal grid map and requests paths to these targets from the path planner.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--MAP--1.1.6">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Frontier Generation Module</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.4</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--MAP--1.3.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL--MAP--1.4.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall implement a frontier-generation module that, upon request from the mission control state machine or planner, returns the set of all cells whose state is UNKNOWN and that are 4-neighbors of at least one FREE cell in the grid map, and shall recompute this set whenever the classification of any cell changes from UNKNOWN to FREE or BLOCKED.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--MAP--1.1.5">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Exploration Target Selection Heuristic</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.5</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--PLAN--1.1</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--PLAN--1.1.2</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL--MAP--1.5.2</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall prioritize exploration frontier targets using a heuristic that:
(1) computes the estimated travel-time component using the same cell-to-cell traversal cost model defined in the path optimality criterion requirement, and
(2) adds a term that prefers frontiers expected to increase the number of newly observable cells,
and shall select targets that minimize this combined heuristic while ensuring that the estimated time to reach and explore the target does not exceed the remaining exploration time defined by the time-aware planning requirement.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <!-- LLRs refining HL--MAP--1.2 Wall Detection -->
  <Requirement ID="LL--MAP--1.2.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Front Wall Detection From Ultrasonic</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--2.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--2.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--2.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--ENV--1.2</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--INTERF--2.3.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall interpret a front ultrasonic distance measurement d as a front wall in the current maze cell if the closed interval [d-12 cm, d+12 cm], derived from the ultrasonic uncertainty model, intersects the expected robot-center-to-wall distance interval for the current cell and pose that is computed from the 17.2 cm cell size and the 11 cm robot diameter.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--MAP--1.2.2">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Side Wall Detection From IR</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--3.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--3.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--3.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--3.4</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--ENV--1.2</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall interpret an active obstacle indication from a left or right infrared sensor as a wall located along the corresponding side of the current maze cell if the robot’s pose is aligned to the maze axes within a configurable angular tolerance not exceeding 10 degrees.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--MAP--1.2.3">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Wall Proximity Thresholding</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--2.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--RELIAB--1.2</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--RELIAB--1.2.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall apply configurable numeric thresholds and hysteresis to filtered ultrasonic distance measurements to distinguish between free space and wall presence, such that single-sample noise or transient spikes do not cause flip-flopping between wall and free classifications.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--MAP--1.2.4">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Wall Avoidance Maneuvers</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--RELIAB--1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--HARDWARE--2.1</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--INTERF--1.2.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL--HARDWARE--1.1.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL--RELIAB--1.1.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall command motor speeds to execute avoidance maneuvers (such as stopping and turning, or arc turns) when front or side wall detections indicate that the predicted robot trajectory would intersect a wall within one cell length, and shall select maneuvers that respect the robot footprint and minimum clearance margin so that collisions are prevented while maintaining progress toward exploration or path-planning goals.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <!-- LLRs refining HL--MAP--1.3 Create Map -->
  <Requirement ID="LL--MAP--1.3.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Grid Map Data Structure</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--ENV--1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--ENV--1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--ENV--1.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--ENV--1.4</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall maintain an in-memory grid map data structure representing the 4x8 maze, where each cell and each inter-cell wall segment is explicitly stored with its classification and can be addressed by integer coordinates (row, column) aligned with the assumed physical maze geometry.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--MAP--1.3.2">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Cell and Wall Update From Sensors</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.4</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--1.1</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--HARDWARE--2.1.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL--POSE--1.1.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL--POSE--1.1.2</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall update the grid map cells and wall segments based on processed ultrasonic and infrared measurements obtained while the pose-estimation module indicates that the robot is located at a cell center or during a transition between adjacent cell centers, marking corresponding walls as PRESENT or ABSENT and updating adjacent cells as FREE if traversed without collision.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--MAP--1.3.3">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Unknown Initialization</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.4</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall initialize all cells and wall segments in the 4x8 grid map to an UNKNOWN classification at system startup prior to any sensor-based observations.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--MAP--1.3.4">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Start Cell Initialization</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.4</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--RUN--1.1</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall designate a fixed coordinate in the grid map as the start cell at initialization, set its classification to FREE, and maintain a record of this coordinate for use in return-to-start and second-run behaviors.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--MAP--1.3.5">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Static Map Assumption</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--ENV--2.1</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--MAP--1.4.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL--MAP--1.4.2</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall treat once-observed wall and free classifications in the grid map as immutable for the duration of a mission, such that:
(1) cell states may change only from UNKNOWN to FREE or UNKNOWN to BLOCKED and shall not revert to UNKNOWN within a mission, and
(2) wall segment states may change only from UNKNOWN to PRESENT or UNKNOWN to ABSENT and shall not change between PRESENT and ABSENT or revert to UNKNOWN within a mission.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--MAP--1.3.6">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Map Completeness Criterion</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--ENV--2.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.4</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall define the map as complete when no cell and no inter-cell wall segment in the grid map remains in the UNKNOWN state, and shall provide a boolean indication of this condition to the mission control state machine.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--MAP--1.3.7">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Grid Map Access Interface</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--PLAN--1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--ENV--3.1</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--SCHED--1.1.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall provide a grid map access interface that offers:
(1) functions to query the classification of any cell and wall segment by (row, column) indices,
(2) functions to update the classification of cells and wall segments, and
(3) an event mechanism or callback registration by which other modules can be notified when specific cells or walls change classification,
and shall ensure that all map queries, updates, and classification-change notifications occur within the context of the periodic control loop execution so that map access is single-threaded and does not require additional synchronization.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <!-- LLRs refining HL--MAP--1.4 Cell Classification -->
  <Requirement ID="LL--MAP--1.4.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Cell Classification Enumeration</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.4</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--MAP--1.3.5</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall represent each maze cell’s state using an enumeration with at least the values {UNKNOWN, FREE, BLOCKED}, shall ensure that each cell in the grid map is always in exactly one of these states, and shall allow cell state transitions only from UNKNOWN to FREE or from UNKNOWN to BLOCKED during a mission.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--MAP--1.4.2">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Wall Segment Classification Enumeration</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.4</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--ENV--1.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--ENV--1.4</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--MAP--1.3.5</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall represent each wall segment between adjacent cells using an enumeration with at least the values {UNKNOWN, PRESENT, ABSENT}, and shall allow wall segment state transitions only from UNKNOWN to PRESENT or from UNKNOWN to ABSENT during a mission, so that once a wall is classified as PRESENT or ABSENT it shall not change state or revert to UNKNOWN in that mission.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--MAP--1.4.3">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Free Cell Confirmation</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.4</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--RELIAB--1.2</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--RELIAB--1.2.2</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall mark a cell as FREE when the robot has successfully traversed into the cell without detecting a collision or blocking wall on the entry face, and no contradictory evidence, as defined by the sensor consistency-check requirement, has been accumulated for that cell.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--MAP--1.4.4">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Blocked Cell Inference</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.4</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--RELIAB--1.1</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall mark a neighboring cell as BLOCKED if a wall segment between the current cell and that neighbor is classified as PRESENT, and shall never issue movement commands that attempt to enter a cell classified as BLOCKED.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <!-- LLRs refining HL--MAP--1.5 Time Constraint -->
  <Requirement ID="LL--MAP--1.5.1">
    <Type>NFR</Type>
    <Name>Global Mapping Time Limit</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.5</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall enforce a global time limit of 5 minutes from the start of exploration, after which it shall cease further exploration moves and signal to the mission control state machine that a timeout condition has occurred to initiate RETURN_TO_START, regardless of mapping completeness.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--MAP--1.5.2">
    <Type>NFR</Type>
    <Name>Time-Aware Planning</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.5</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--PLAN--1.1</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--MAP--1.5.3</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall estimate remaining exploration time based on elapsed time and a configurable parameter representing the nominal time to traverse one cell at exploration speed, and shall avoid selecting exploration targets that cannot be reasonably reached and mapped before the 5 minute exploration time limit.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--MAP--1.5.3">
    <Type>NFR</Type>
    <Name>Nominal Cell Traversal Duration Parameter</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.5</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--PLAN--1.1</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall maintain a configurable parameter representing the nominal time required to traverse one maze cell at exploration speed, expressed in milliseconds, and shall make this parameter available to time-aware planning and exploration modules for remaining-time estimation.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <!-- LLRs refining HL--PLAN--1.1 Path Planning -->
  <Requirement ID="LL--PLAN--1.1.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Cell-Based Path Planner</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--PLAN--1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.4</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--MAP--1.3.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall implement a cell-based path planning algorithm (such as Dijkstra or A*) operating on the 4x8 grid map, where nodes correspond to FREE cells and edges connect orthogonally adjacent FREE cells (4-connected grid) that are not separated by PRESENT walls.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--PLAN--1.1.2">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Path Optimality Criterion</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--PLAN--1.1</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall define path optimality as minimizing total traversal cost, where each move between orthogonally adjacent FREE cells has a non-negative cost that may be parameterized to distinguish straight-travel and turning penalties, and shall compute paths that minimize the sum of such costs between a given start and goal region.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--PLAN--1.1.3">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Goal Region Handling</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--PLAN--1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--ENV--3.1</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--ENV--3.1.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall treat the selected 2x2 goal region as a set of up to four FREE goal cells and shall compute an optimal path from a given start cell to any of these goal cells, selecting the path with minimal traversal cost.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--PLAN--1.1.4">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Replanning Capability</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--PLAN--1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.3</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--MAP--1.3.7</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall recompute planned paths whenever newly acquired map information marks previously assumed FREE cells or ABSENT walls as BLOCKED or PRESENT and the current path would otherwise traverse those blocked cells or walls, using the grid map access interface to detect invalidation events.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--PLAN--1.1.5">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Planning Failure Reporting</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--PLAN--1.1</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall detect and signal a planning failure when no path exists between the current cell and the desired target or goal region in the current map, so that higher-level logic can report failure or select alternative behavior.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <!-- LLRs refining HL--RUN--1.1 Return to Start -->
  <Requirement ID="LL--RUN--1.1.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Return Path Computation</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--RUN--1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--PLAN--1.1</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--EVENT--1.1.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall provide a return-to-start service that, when invoked by the mission control state machine after receipt of either an EXPLORATION_COMPLETED event or an EXPLORATION_TIMEOUT event, computes a path from the robot’s current cell to the designated start cell using the path planning algorithm and current grid map.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--RUN--1.1.2">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Return Path Execution</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--RUN--1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--HARDWARE--2.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--RELIAB--1.1</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--INTERF--1.2.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL--HARDWARE--2.1.2</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL--RELIAB--1.1.2</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall execute the computed return path cell by cell by issuing motor speed commands that move the robot between cell centers using motion primitives, while monitoring sensors to avoid collisions and triggering replanning if the path becomes invalid due to updated map information.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <!-- LLRs refining HL--RUN--1.2 Second Run and HL--RUN--1.3 Efficient Path Execution -->
  <Requirement ID="LL--RUN--1.2.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Second Run Initialization</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--RUN--1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--RUN--1.3</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--RUN--1.1.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall initiate the SECOND_RUN state in the mission control state machine after the robot has returned to the start cell and exploration has been declared complete by the exploration module.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--RUN--1.2.2">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Fastest Path Computation</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--RUN--1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--RUN--1.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--PLAN--1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--ENV--3.1</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--PLAN--1.1.2</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL--ENV--3.1.2</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall compute the fastest path from the start cell to the selected goal region using the grid map and path planner by configuring the traversal cost model parameters so that the resulting path minimizes an estimate of physical travel time during the second run.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--RUN--1.2.3">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Fast Path Motion Profile</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--RUN--1.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--HARDWARE--2.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--HARDWARE--2.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--RELIAB--1.1</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--HARDWARE--2.3.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL--RELIAB--1.1.2</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall execute the fastest path using motor speed commands that increase translational speed relative to exploration while limiting the commanded speeds to computed maximum permissible values that ensure the robot can safely stop before a wall given the configured sensor sampling rate, emergency-stop threshold, and ultrasonic uncertainty.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--RUN--1.2.4">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Second Run Success Criteria</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--RUN--1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--ENV--3.1</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall declare the second run a success when the robot reaches any FREE cell in the 2x2 goal region following the fastest path without any detected collision; otherwise it shall declare the second run a failure.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--RUN--1.2.5">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Second Run Status Reporting</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--RUN--1.2</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall provide a boolean or enumerated status output indicating success or failure of the second run upon completion or abort of the SECOND_RUN state for use by the mission control state machine and external reporting.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <!-- LLRs refining HL--RELIAB--1.1 Collision Avoidance -->
  <Requirement ID="LL--RELIAB--1.1.1">
    <Type>NFR</Type>
    <Name>Minimum Wall Clearance</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--RELIAB--1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--HARDWARE--1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--ENV--1.2</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--INTERF--2.3.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall enforce a configurable minimum clearance margin M &gt; 0 cm between the robot’s circular footprint of radius 5.5 cm and any wall position derived from the grid map, where M shall be selected to cover estimated worst-case pose and wall localization errors based on the ultrasonic uncertainty model, and shall ensure that planned and executed trajectories do not violate this clearance when following ideal commands.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--RELIAB--1.1.2">
    <Type>NFR</Type>
    <Name>Emergency Stop on Imminent Collision</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--RELIAB--1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--2.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--3.1</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--INTERF--1.2.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL--RELIAB--1.2.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall immediately command both motors to speed 0 by invoking the motor command interface if filtered sensor data indicates an obstacle or wall within a configurable emergency distance threshold shorter than the nominal stopping distance at the current speed, and shall not resume movement until a new safe trajectory has been established.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <!-- LLRs refining HL--RELIAB--1.2 Sensor Noise Handling -->
  <Requirement ID="LL--RELIAB--1.2.1">
    <Type>NFR</Type>
    <Name>Sensor Sampling and Filtering</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--RELIAB--1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--2.3</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--SCHED--1.1.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall sample ultrasonic and infrared sensors at a configurable rate in the range [10, 50] Hz, with a default value of 20 Hz and timing jitter not exceeding a specified tolerance, and shall apply temporal filtering (such as moving average or median filters) to the sampled data to reduce the effect of random noise before using the data for wall detection or planning decisions, and shall perform this sampling once per iteration of the periodic control loop.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--RELIAB--1.2.2">
    <Type>NFR</Type>
    <Name>Consistency Checks on Sensor Data</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--RELIAB--1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.3</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall compare new sensor-based wall observations against existing map entries and shall treat large, isolated discrepancies as potential sensor errors, requiring at least N configurable consecutive sensor readings that indicate a wall where the map currently stores FREE or ABSENT before changing the established wall or cell classification, where N shall be an integer greater than or equal to 2 with a documented default value of 3 and a recommended configuration range 2 ≤ N ≤ 10.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <!-- LLRs refining HL--INTERF--1.1 Sensor Processing -->
  <Requirement ID="LL--INTERF--1.1.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Sensor Abstraction Layer</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--2.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--3.1</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--RELIAB--1.2.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall implement a sensor abstraction layer that wraps the ultrasonic_get_distance and infrared_get_dsl_status/infrared_get_dsr_status functions and exposes normalized sensor data structures to higher-level modules, including for each control cycle:
(1) an ultrasonic measurement represented as (distance_cm, timestamp), where distance_cm is a float in centimeters in the robot-forward frame, and
(2) infrared measurements represented as (left_flag, right_flag, timestamp), where each flag is a binary obstacle indication and timestamp is the acquisition time.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--INTERF--1.1.2">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Invalid Sensor Reading Handling</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--RELIAB--1.2</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall detect invalid or out-of-range sensor return values, such as negative distances or implementation-specific saturation codes, and shall ignore these readings or replace them with safe default estimates rather than using them directly for mapping or control decisions.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <!-- LLRs refining HL--INTERF--1.2 Actuator Control -->
  <Requirement ID="LL--INTERF--1.2.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Motor Command Interface</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--HARDWARE--2.1</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--SCHED--1.1.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall control the differential drive motors exclusively via the function motor_set(uint8_t left_speed, uint8_t right_speed), using integer speed values in the range [0,100] for each motor, and shall invoke motor_set at most once per iteration of the periodic control loop at the control loop frequency.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--INTERF--1.2.2">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Speed Command Rate Limiting</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--HARDWARE--2.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--RELIAB--1.1</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall limit the rate of change of successive motor_set speed commands by enforcing configurable maximum increments per control cycle for left and right speeds to avoid abrupt accelerations or decelerations that could cause wheel slippage or loss of control.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <!-- LLRs refining HL--INTERF--2.1, 2.2, 2.3 Ultrasonic -->
  <Requirement ID="LL--INTERF--2.1.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Ultrasonic Distance Acquisition</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--2.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--2.2</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--RELIAB--1.2.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall, once per sensor sampling period defined by the noise-handling requirement and synchronized with the periodic control loop, call ultrasonic_get_distance() and interpret the returned float value as the distance in centimeters to the nearest front obstacle along the sensor beam in the robot-forward frame.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--INTERF--2.3.1">
    <Type>NFR</Type>
    <Name>Ultrasonic Uncertainty Model</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--2.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--RELIAB--1.2</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall model each ultrasonic distance measurement as having an uncertainty interval of at least ±12 cm around the measured distance value and shall incorporate this interval into wall distance estimation, collision risk computations, and clearance-margin evaluations.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <!-- LLRs refining HL--INTERF--3.x IR sensors -->
  <Requirement ID="LL--INTERF--3.1.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>IR Status Acquisition</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--3.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--3.2</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--RELIAB--1.2.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall, at each sensor sampling period synchronized with the periodic control loop, call infrared_get_dsl_status() and infrared_get_dsr_status() and interpret each returned uint8_t value as a binary obstacle detection flag for the respective left and right infrared sensors.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--INTERF--3.3.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>IR Effective Range Assumption</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--3.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.2</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall assume that a positive obstacle indication from an infrared sensor corresponds to an obstacle located approximately 4 cm from the sensor along its measurement direction and shall use this nominal distance when inferring side wall positions in the grid map.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--INTERF--3.4.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>IR Orientation Compensation</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--3.4</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.2</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall account for the approximately 25 degree mounting angle of each infrared sensor relative to the robot front direction when transforming infrared obstacle detections into equivalent lateral wall distances and positions in the maze reference frame.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <!-- LLRs refining HL--HARDWARE--1.1 Robot Shape -->
  <Requirement ID="LL--HARDWARE--1.1.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Robot Footprint Model</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--HARDWARE--1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--ENV--1.2</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall model the robot as a circle of radius 5.5 cm when checking for possible collisions with walls located at cell boundaries spaced approximately 17.2 cm apart and when evaluating clearance against the minimum clearance margin.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <!-- LLRs refining HL--HARDWARE--2.1 Differential Drive -->
  <Requirement ID="LL--HARDWARE--2.1.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Differential Drive Kinematics</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--HARDWARE--2.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--HARDWARE--2.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--HARDWARE--2.3</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--INTERF--1.2.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall implement kinematic equations for a differential drive robot to estimate changes in robot orientation and position over time based on the left and right motor speed commands and the control-loop period T or measured cycle duration from the scheduling module, without assuming constant rotational speed.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--HARDWARE--2.1.2">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Cell-Center Motion Primitives</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--HARDWARE--2.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--ENV--1.2</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--HARDWARE--2.1.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall provide motion primitives that move the robot from one maze cell center to an adjacent cell center and turn in place to discrete headings aligned with maze axes, using sequences of motor_set commands whose durations and speeds are derived from the differential-drive kinematics and cell dimension of approximately 17.2 cm.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <!-- LLRs refining HL--HARDWARE--2.3 Translational Velocity -->
  <Requirement ID="LL--HARDWARE--2.3.1">
    <Type>NFR</Type>
    <Name>Speed Limitation for Safety</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--HARDWARE--2.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--RELIAB--1.1</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--RELIAB--1.1.2</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL--INTERF--2.3.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall constrain the commanded motor speeds such that the resulting translational speed does not exceed a configured maximum below the 200 cm/s hardware capability, where this maximum speed is computed to ensure that, given the configured sensor sampling rate, emergency-stop distance threshold, and ultrasonic uncertainty, the robot can safely stop before reaching a detected wall.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <!-- LLRs refining HL--ENV--1.x Maze properties -->
  <Requirement ID="LL--ENV--1.1.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Grid Coordinate System</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--ENV--1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.3</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall define a grid coordinate system with 4 rows and 8 columns for the maze, with a consistent convention for mapping physical positions to cell indices, such as defining row 0, column 0 as the start cell, and shall use this convention consistently across mapping, planning, and control modules.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--ENV--1.2.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Cell Geometry Parameters</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--ENV--1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.3</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall use the approximate cell dimension of 17.2 cm when transforming between estimated traveled distances and transitions between maze cell centers for pose estimation, motion primitive generation, and grid map updates.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--ENV--1.3.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Wall Geometry Parameters</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--ENV--1.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.2</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall use an approximate wall thickness of 1.6 cm when reasoning about the physical extent of walls relative to the robot footprint in collision and clearance checks.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--ENV--1.4.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Inter-Cell Wall Indexing</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--ENV--1.4</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.3</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall index possible wall positions as boundaries between horizontally and vertically adjacent cells and shall store wall presence or absence for each such boundary in the grid map.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--ENV--3.1.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Goal Region Identification</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--ENV--3.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.4</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall, upon completion of exploration, identify as candidate goal regions all contiguous 2x2 blocks of cells that are all classified as FREE and reachable from the start cell in the grid map.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--ENV--3.1.2">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Goal Region Selection</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--ENV--3.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--PLAN--1.1</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--PLAN--1.1.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall, when multiple candidate 2x2 FREE regions exist, select as the maze goal region the one that minimizes the optimal path cost from the start cell according to the traversal cost metric defined for the path planner, and shall provide this selected region to the second-run planning module.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <!-- Additional LLRs -->

  <Requirement ID="LL--POSE--1.1.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Cell-Level Pose Estimation</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--HARDWARE--2.1</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--HARDWARE--2.1.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL--SCHED--1.1.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall maintain an estimate of the robot’s current maze cell index (row, column) and discrete heading aligned with the maze axes, updated in each control loop cycle by integrating the differential drive kinematics over the control-loop period T or measured cycle duration provided by the scheduling module and the issued motor speed commands.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--POSE--1.1.2">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Pose Correction Using Map Features</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--HARDWARE--2.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--RELIAB--1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.3</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--MAP--1.2.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL--MAP--1.2.2</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall correct accumulated orientation and position error in the pose estimate when the robot is aligned with maze axes and wall detections indicate proximity to known cell boundaries, by snapping the estimated heading to the nearest axis-aligned direction and adjusting the position to the nearest cell center consistent with the wall observations.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--POSE--1.1.3">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Cell Center Entry Notification</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.3</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--POSE--1.1.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall detect when the pose estimate crosses from one cell center to an adjacent cell center and shall notify the mapping module of the new current cell index so that cell and wall updates can be associated with the correct cell transition.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--EVENT--1.1.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Exploration Status Events</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.5</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--RUN--1.1</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--MAP--1.3.6</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL--MAP--1.5.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall implement an exploration-status module, integrated with the mission control state machine, that publishes EXPLORATION_COMPLETED and EXPLORATION_TIMEOUT events by enqueuing corresponding event records into a system event queue accessible to the mission control and return-to-start modules when, respectively, the map completeness criterion indicates a complete map or the global exploration time limit is reached.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--SCHED--1.1.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Periodic Control Loop Scheduling</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--PLAN--1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--RELIAB--1.2</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall implement a periodic control loop with a configurable period T such that the control loop frequency equals the sensor sampling rate defined in the sensor sampling requirement, and in each cycle it shall:
(1) acquire sensor readings via the sensor abstraction layer,
(2) update the grid map using the mapping module,
(3) update the mission control state machine,
(4) compute or update the current path as required by the active state, and
(5) issue motor_set commands via the motion control module.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--INIT--1.1.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Initialization Completion Signaling</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--1.2</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall implement an initialization module that, after all required hardware and software initialization routines have successfully completed, sets an INIT_COMPLETED flag or publishes an INIT_COMPLETED event within the main execution context, and the mission control state machine shall only transition from IDLE to EXPLORE after this indication is present.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>
</Requirements>


[2026-05-20--17:28:33]Agent: <Design>
    <Components version="1">
        <Component>
            <ID>CMP--1</ID>
            <Name>Mission Control State Machine</Name>
            <Purpose>
                Central mission coordinator implementing the top-level exploration mission logic as a deterministic state machine with states {IDLE, EXPLORE, RETURN_TO_START, SECOND_RUN, COMPLETED}. It drives frontier-based exploration, triggers return-to-start and second-run behaviors, and coordinates with mapping, planning, motion control, initialization, and event modules.

                Responsibilities:
                - Maintain and update the mission state machine each control loop cycle.
                - In IDLE: wait for initialization completion and sufficient initial sensor data before starting exploration.
                - In EXPLORE: request frontier targets, request paths to selected targets, and command motion primitives to follow paths; monitor map completeness and global exploration time limit; trigger exploration completion or timeout handling.
                - In RETURN_TO_START: invoke return-to-start service to compute and execute a path to the start cell; monitor for planning failures and arrival.
                - In SECOND_RUN: invoke fastest-path planning to the selected goal region; command motion control to execute the path at higher speed; monitor second-run success/failure.
                - In COMPLETED: stop issuing new motion commands and maintain final second-run status for external reporting.
                - Interface with the event system to consume EXPLORATION_COMPLETED and EXPLORATION_TIMEOUT events and to expose second-run status.
            </Purpose>
            <ConnectedComponents>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--2</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_State</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Current mission control state enumeration {IDLE, EXPLORE, RETURN_TO_START, SECOND_RUN, COMPLETED}. Published once per control loop iteration for diagnostic and coordination purposes.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_ActivePathRequest</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Path request structure sent to the path planner when in EXPLORE, RETURN_TO_START, or SECOND_RUN. Contains:
                                - request_id (monotonic integer),
                                - request_type {EXPLORE_TARGET, RETURN_TO_START, SECOND_RUN},
                                - start_cell (row, col) equal to current pose cell,
                                - goal_spec:
                                  * for EXPLORE_TARGET: single target cell (row, col) or list of candidate frontier cells,
                                  * for RETURN_TO_START: designated start cell (row, col),
                                  * for SECOND_RUN: selected goal region descriptor (set of goal cells).
                                - cost_model_id selecting traversal cost parameters.
                                The signal is logically a method call from Mission Control into the Path Planner via the Motion Control / planning interface.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_MotionCommand</Name>
                            <Description>
                                High-level motion command issued to Motion Control.
                                Fields:
                                - command_type: {FOLLOW_PATH, STOP},
                                - path_id: identifier of current planned path (for FOLLOW_PATH),
                                - execution_mode: {EXPLORATION_SPEED, SECOND_RUN_SPEED},
                                - emergency_only: boolean specifying whether only collision avoidance / emergency stop is allowed to override.
                                Emitted whenever state machine changes behavior or new path becomes active.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_SecondRunStatusOut</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Enumerated second-run status value exported for external reporting:
                                {NOT_STARTED, RUNNING, SUCCESS, FAILURE, ABORTED}.
                                In COMPLETED state, this value must remain constant until reset.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_ExplorationStatus</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Aggregated exploration status information originating from Frontier Generation, Grid Map, Time Limit, and Event modules and provided via the Exploration Status / Return-to-Start services. Contains:
                                - exploration_complete (bool),
                                - exploration_timeout (bool),
                                - last_status_event: {NONE, EXPLORATION_COMPLETED, EXPLORATION_TIMEOUT},
                                - map_complete (bool),
                                - remaining_exploration_time_ms (int32).
                                Consumed in EXPLORE to trigger transition to RETURN_TO_START and to decide between completion vs timeout reason.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_InitCompleted</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Boolean or event flag indicating that system initialization has completed successfully.
                                Set by Initialization module exactly once near startup, and latched until mission end.
                                Mission Control transitions from IDLE only when this flag is true and at least one valid sensor sample has been received.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_ValidSensorsAvailable</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Boolean flag, produced by Sensor Abstraction and Mapping, indicating that at least one valid set of ultrasonic and IR measurements has been obtained in the current mission.
                                Enables automatic transition from IDLE to EXPLORE when combined with InitCompleted.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_PathPlannerResult</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Path planner result for the most recent request:
                                - request_id: echoes MC_ActivePathRequest.request_id,
                                - status: {SUCCESS, FAILURE_NO_PATH},
                                - path_id: identifier of stored path if SUCCESS,
                                - traversal_cost: float total cost of path,
                                - estimated_travel_time_ms: int32 estimated real-world traversal time (taking current cost model),
                                - invalidation_token: used for replanning triggers.
                                Used by Mission Control to:
                                - decide next frontier target in EXPLORE,
                                - enter RETURN_TO_START execution or report planning failure,
                                - enter SECOND_RUN execution and compute success/failure.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_PathExecutionStatus</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Feedback from Motion Control while following a path:
                                - path_id,
                                - current_cell (row, col),
                                - goal_reached (bool),
                                - aborted (bool),
                                - abort_reason: {COLLISION_RISK, PATH_INVALIDATED, EMERGENCY_STOP, OTHER},
                                - second_run_goal_reached (bool) indicating success condition for second run.
                                Used for transitions to next mission state and for second-run success criteria.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_GoalRegionSelection</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Selected goal region descriptor from Goal Region Selection/Environment module:
                                - region_id,
                                - goal_cells: list of up to 4 cells (row, col),
                                - reachable (bool).
                                Consumed upon entering SECOND_RUN to request fastest path.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>

                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--11</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_ExplorationState</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Exploration phase hints (e.g., ACTIVE, RETURNING, SECOND_RUN, COMPLETED) passed to Exploration Status / Time Limit module.
                                Supports consistent event generation and timing resets.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_ExplorationEvents</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Exploration events enqueued in the system event queue:
                                - EXPLORATION_COMPLETED,
                                - EXPLORATION_TIMEOUT.
                                Received logically as part of MC_ExplorationStatus but conceptually originating from the Exploration Status module.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>

                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--12</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_ControlLoopHook</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Control-loop stage callback registration; Mission Control registers its update() as the third stage in the scheduling order (after sensor and mapping).
                                No data payload; used only to guarantee invocation order each period T.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_ControlLoopTick</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Periodic control loop tick notification from Scheduler, once per loop.
                                Triggers Mission Control evaluation of state machine and associated actions.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
            </ConnectedComponents>
            <Execution>
                - Executed once per control-loop iteration after:
                  1) Sensor sampling/filtering and abstraction,
                  2) Grid map update and exploration-status/time computations.
                - Pre-conditions:
                  * Scheduling module has invoked MissionControl_Update() in the correct order.
                  * All inputs (InitCompleted, sensor validity, exploration status, planner/motion feedback) from the previous cycle are latched and available.
                - Execution steps (per cycle):
                  1) Evaluate current state and any new events (init completed, exploration completed/timeout, path results, path execution status, second-run completion).
                  2) Perform state transition logic, ensuring exactly one deterministic transition per cycle at most.
                  3) For the resulting active state, compute required control actions:
                     - issue path requests where needed,
                     - issue motion commands or STOP,
                     - update second-run status.
                  4) Persist updated state and status variables in module-local static context.
            </Execution>
            <Timing>
                - Updated strictly once per periodic control loop cycle, with period T (sensor sampling rate) as defined by the Scheduler (LL--SCHED--1.1.1).
                - State transitions are evaluated and applied within a single control cycle and are thus deterministic with respect to the ordered inputs within that cycle.
                - Time-dependent behavior (global 5-minute limit, remaining exploration time, exploration timeout) depends on wall-clock or cycle-count maintained by Exploration Status/Time Limit module; Mission Control reacts to their boolean/time flags without performing its own timing.
            </Timing>
            <Invariants>
                - State is always one of {IDLE, EXPLORE, RETURN_TO_START, SECOND_RUN, COMPLETED}.
                - Exactly one state is active at any time.
                - Once COMPLETED is entered, Mission Control shall no longer issue FOLLOW_PATH motion commands; only STOP commands are allowed.
                - SecondRunStatusOut is:
                  * NOT_STARTED in states {IDLE, EXPLORE, RETURN_TO_START},
                  * RUNNING only in SECOND_RUN while path execution is ongoing,
                  * SUCCESS or FAILURE latched in COMPLETED.
                - IDLE-&gt;EXPLORE transition only allowed if:
                  * InitCompleted == true, AND
                  * ValidSensorsAvailable == true.
                - RETURN_TO_START cannot be entered before EXPLORE has been active at least once.
            </Invariants>
            <Failures>
                - Planning failure in RETURN_TO_START:
                  * Trigger: PathPlannerResult.status == FAILURE_NO_PATH for a RETURN_TO_START request.
                  * Behavior: Mission Control records a return failure, commands STOP to motion control, and transitions to COMPLETED with SecondRunStatusOut set to FAILURE (mission failure).
                - Planning failure in SECOND_RUN:
                  * Trigger: PathPlannerResult.status == FAILURE_NO_PATH for a SECOND_RUN fastest-path request.
                  * Behavior: Mission Control does not start second-run motion, transitions to COMPLETED with SecondRunStatusOut set to FAILURE.
                - Path execution abort:
                  * Trigger: PathExecutionStatus.aborted == true.
                  * In RETURN_TO_START: attempt replanning once (through Return-To-Start Service); if repeated failure, transition to COMPLETED with SecondRunStatusOut == FAILURE.
                  * In SECOND_RUN: treat as second-run failure, transition to COMPLETED.
                - Inconsistent inputs:
                  * If exploration_complete and exploration_timeout flags are both true in the same cycle, Mission Control favors EXPLORATION_COMPLETED as completion reason, logs diagnostic, and continues deterministically by entering RETURN_TO_START.
            </Failures>
            <DerivedFrom>
                LL--MAP--1.1.1
                LL--MAP--1.1.2
                LL--MAP--1.1.3
                LL--MAP--1.1.4
                LL--MAP--1.5.1
                LL--MAP--1.5.2
                LL--MAP--1.5.3
                LL--PLAN--1.1.1
                LL--RUN--1.1.1
                LL--RUN--1.1.2
                LL--RUN--1.2.1
                LL--RUN--1.2.2
                LL--RUN--1.2.3
                LL--RUN--1.2.4
                LL--RUN--1.2.5
                LL--EVENT--1.1.1
                LL--SCHED--1.1.1
                LL--INIT--1.1.1
            </DerivedFrom>
        </Component>

        <Component>
            <ID>CMP--2</ID>
            <Name>Motion Control and Path Execution</Name>
            <Purpose>
                Translate high-level paths into low-level motor_set commands using cell-center motion primitives, while enforcing safety constraints, emergency stop behavior, and speed limitations for exploration and second-run modes.

                Responsibilities:
                - Receive planned paths (sequence of FREE cells/headings) from Path Planner via Mission Control.
                - Execute paths cell by cell using motion primitives (forward moves, in-place turns) consistent with 17.2 cm cell size and differential-drive kinematics.
                - Enforce:
                  * motor_set usage and rate limits,
                  * maximum allowable speeds for exploration vs second run,
                  * speed change rate limiting.
                - Perform runtime collision avoidance and emergency stops based on sensor-derived distances.
                - Request replanning via Mission Control when paths are invalidated or blocked.
                - Provide continuous path execution status feedback to Mission Control.
            </Purpose>
            <ConnectedComponents>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--1</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_PathExecutionStatus</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Status update of currently executed path:
                                - path_id,
                                - current_cell (row, col) as provided by Pose Estimation,
                                - goal_reached (bool),
                                - aborted (bool),
                                - abort_reason: {NONE, COLLISION_RISK, PATH_INVALIDATED, EMERGENCY_STOP, OTHER},
                                - second_run_goal_reached (bool) used to determine SECOND_RUN success.
                                Update rate: once per control cycle while executing a path.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_MotionCommand</Name>
                            <Description>
                                High-level motion command from Mission Control:
                                - command_type: {FOLLOW_PATH, STOP},
                                - path_id,
                                - execution_mode: {EXPLORATION_SPEED, SECOND_RUN_SPEED},
                                - emergency_only: if true, Motion Control only ensures emergency stop and does not initiate new motion.
                                On FOLLOW_PATH, Motion Control loads associated path and starts executing from current pose.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>

                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--5</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_NewPathInvalidationSubscription</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Registration for notifications when currently executed path becomes invalidated due to map updates. Contains current path_id and invalidation_token.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_PathInvalidated</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Notification that part of the current path traverses cells or walls newly marked BLOCKED or PRESENT.
                                Fields:
                                - path_id,
                                - invalidated_index: index of first invalid step,
                                - reason: {CELL_BLOCKED, WALL_PRESENT}.
                                Motion Control reacts by aborting path execution and informing Mission Control.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>

                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--7</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_MotionPrimitiveUsage</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Optional debug/telemetry signal specifying which motion primitive was selected this cycle, including:
                                - primitive_type: {FORWARD_CELL, TURN_LEFT_90, TURN_RIGHT_90, TURN_180},
                                - target_cell (row, col),
                                - expected_duration_ms.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_DriveKinematicsParams</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Differential-drive parameters from Hardware Kinematics:
                                - wheel_base (cm),
                                - max_translational_speed_exploration (cm/s),
                                - max_translational_speed_second_run (cm/s),
                                - control_loop_period_ms (int).
                                Used to convert primitive distances/angles into motor_set left/right speeds and durations (over multiple cycles).
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>

                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--4</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_EmergencyStopEvent</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Flag or event indicating that motion has been halted due to emergency-stop logic.
                                Includes:
                                - cause_distance_cm,
                                - sensor_source: {ULTRASONIC, IR_LEFT, IR_RIGHT, COMBINED},
                                - threshold_cm.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_SensorDistanceAndWalls</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Aggregated filtered sensor information used for collision-checking:
                                - ultrasonic_distance_cm (float),
                                - ultrasonic_valid (bool),
                                - ir_left_flag, ir_right_flag (bool),
                                - latest_pose (cell index and heading).
                                Includes derived wall distance estimates accounting for ultrasonic uncertainty and IR effective range and angles.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>

                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--8</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>motor_set_call</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Invocation of motor_set(uint8_t left_speed, uint8_t right_speed) according to LL--INTERF--1.2.1.
                                Motion Control enforces:
                                - at most one call per control-loop iteration,
                                - left_speed and right_speed within [0,100],
                                - speed increments limited per cycle by configuration.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_MotorCommandConstraints</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Configuration inputs for:
                                - max_speed_exploration (0-100),
                                - max_speed_second_run (0-100),
                                - max_delta_speed_per_cycle_left (uint8_t),
                                - max_delta_speed_per_cycle_right (uint8_t),
                                - current_sensor_sampling_rate_hz,
                                - emergency_stop_distance_threshold_cm.
                                Derived from Speed Limitation, Reliability, and Hardware modules.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>

                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--10</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_PoseUsage</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Indicates which next cell Motion Control expects the robot to reach, for Pose Estimation to cross-check transitions.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_CurrentPose</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Current pose estimate (row, col, discrete heading) from Pose Estimation, used to determine completion of a cell primitive and to decide heading corrections for turns.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>

                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--12</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_ControlLoopHook</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Motion Control registers its update() to be executed as stage 5 of the control loop (after Mission Control).
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_ControlLoopTick</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Control loop tick to perform one step of primitive execution and to issue at most one motor_set call.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
            </ConnectedComponents>
            <Execution>
                - Called once per control loop after Mission Control.
                - If MC_MotionCommand.command_type == STOP:
                  * Immediately command motor_set(0,0) if any non-zero speed is active.
                  * Clear internal active path execution state.
                  * Set PathExecutionStatus.aborted = false, goal_reached as per pose.
                - If FOLLOW_PATH:
                  * If path just started, initialize:
                    - index of next waypoint cell,
                    - current primitive state (IDLE),
                    - execution_mode (EXPLORATION_SPEED or SECOND_RUN_SPEED).
                  * For current primitive:
                    1) If primitive is IDLE:
                       - Determine difference between current pose and next waypoint:
                         * If different heading: schedule TURN primitive first.
                         * Else: schedule FORWARD_CELL primitive.
                    2) For TURN primitives:
                       - Use differential-drive kinematics and configured speeds to determine:
                         * motor_set commands (e.g., left_speed = v, right_speed = 100-v or symmetric),
                         * number of cycles to achieve ±90° or 180° based on control_loop_period_ms.
                       - Continue issuing same command until pose-correction module reports heading aligned within tolerance; then set primitive complete.
                    3) For FORWARD_CELL primitives:
                       - Map 17.2 cm move into approximate duration cycles given current translational speed and T.
                       - Use sensor-based emergency stop: if any wall or obstacle is predicted within one cell length minus safety margin, adjust speeds or stop.
                       - When Pose Estimation indicates crossing to target cell center, complete primitive.
                    4) On primitive completion:
                       - Advance path index; if at path end, mark goal_reached and send PathExecutionStatus.goal_reached = true.
                - At each cycle:
                  * Enforce speed limits:
                    - Lookup allowed max speed per mode from MC_MotorCommandConstraints and Hardware constraints.
                    - Clip desired left/right speeds to not exceed these max values.
                  * Enforce per-cycle rate limiting:
                    - NewSpeed = min(old_speed + max_delta, max(old_speed - max_delta, desired_speed)).
                  * Before issuing motor_set:
                    - Check emergency-stop condition using MC_SensorDistanceAndWalls:
                      * If any distance estimate (accounting for ultrasonic ±12 cm) &lt; emergency_stop_distance_threshold_cm,
                        issue motor_set(0,0) and raise EmergencyStopEvent and PathExecutionStatus.aborted = true with abort_reason EMERGENCY_STOP.
            </Execution>
            <Timing>
                - Exactly one motor_set call per control loop cycle, as required by LL--INTERF--1.2.1.
                - Path execution primitives are time-discretized to integral multiples of the control loop period T.
                - Emergency stop reaction occurs within one control loop cycle after detection of an imminent collision.
                - Speed change rate limiting applied per cycle ensures smooth accelerations and decelerations.
            </Timing>
            <Invariants>
                - motor_set is never called more than once per control loop iteration.
                - Commanded speeds always satisfy 0 ≤ left_speed,right_speed ≤ configured global max &lt;= hardware 100% and below safety-limited translational speed.
                - When PathExecutionStatus.aborted == true, motor_set(0,0) must have been issued in the same or previous cycle and no new FOLLOW_PATH primitives are started until Mission Control issues a new MC_MotionCommand.
                - Motion primitives align robot heading only to the discrete set {0°, 90°, 180°, 270°} (maze axes) using Pose Estimation corrections.
            </Invariants>
            <Failures>
                - Path invalidation:
                  * Trigger: MC_PathInvalidated received for active path_id.
                  * Behavior: Immediately halt forward primitives, gradually stop motors within one or two cycles (respecting rate limiting but prioritizing safety), set PathExecutionStatus.aborted = true, abort_reason = PATH_INVALIDATED.
                - Collision risk during execution:
                  * Trigger: MC_SensorDistanceAndWalls indicates obstacle within one cell length (taking into account clearance margin M, ultrasonic ±12 cm, and IR geometry).
                  * Behavior: emergency stop as described, mark aborted with abort_reason COLLISION_RISK, report to Mission Control.
                - Pose inconsistency:
                  * If Pose Estimation indicates the robot has overshot target cell by more than half cell (distance), Motion Control declares the primitive failed, stops motion, marks PathExecutionStatus.aborted and abort_reason OTHER, and waits for new commands.
            </Failures>
            <DerivedFrom>
                LL--MAP--1.2.4
                LL--MAP--1.4.4
                LL--RUN--1.1.2
                LL--RUN--1.2.3
                LL--RELIAB--1.1.1
                LL--RELIAB--1.1.2
                LL--INTERF--1.2.1
                LL--INTERF--1.2.2
                LL--HARDWARE--2.1.1
                LL--HARDWARE--2.1.2
                LL--HARDWARE--2.3.1
                LL--SCHED--1.1.1
            </DerivedFrom>
        </Component>

        <Component>
            <ID>CMP--3</ID>
            <Name>Sensor Abstraction and Filtering</Name>
            <Purpose>
                Provide a unified, filtered view of ultrasonic and infrared sensor data to higher-level modules, handling sampling, timestamping, invalid reading detection, and basic temporal filtering.

                Responsibilities:
                - Periodically sample ultrasonic and IR sensors synchronized with the control loop.
                - Apply temporal filtering (moving average or median) to reduce noise.
                - Detect invalid/ out-of-range readings and discard or replace with safe defaults.
                - Generate normalized measurement structures:
                  * ultrasonic: (distance_cm, timestamp, valid),
                  * IR: (left_flag, right_flag, timestamp).
                - Provide configurable sampling rate within [10,50] Hz with default 20 Hz and bounded jitter.
            </Purpose>
            <ConnectedComponents>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--8</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>SA_SensorAPICalls</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Calls to low-level hardware functions:
                                - ultrasonic_get_distance() → float distance_cm,
                                - infrared_get_dsl_status() → uint8_t left_flag_raw,
                                - infrared_get_dsr_status() → uint8_t right_flag_raw.
                                Invoked once per sampling period synchronized with control loop.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>SA_HardwareSensorValues</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Return values from underlying sensor drivers; interpreted according to sensor documentation (e.g., negative values or special codes for invalid data).
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>

                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--4</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>SA_NormalizedUltrasonic</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Filtered ultrasonic measurement structure:
                                - distance_cm: float, average or median over last N valid samples,
                                - timestamp: control loop tick or absolute time,
                                - valid: boolean; false if all samples in window invalid.
                                Distance correction for uncertainty is not applied here; left to mapping/collision modules.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>SA_NormalizedIR</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Filtered IR measurements:
                                - left_flag: bool (obstacle present) after debouncing and optional temporal filter,
                                - right_flag: bool,
                                - timestamp.
                                Raw 0/1 values are smoothed to avoid transient spikes.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>SA_FilterConfig</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Configuration values:
                                - sampling_rate_hz (10-50),
                                - filter_type: {MOVING_AVERAGE, MEDIAN},
                                - filter_window_size (integer, e.g. 3-5 samples),
                                - invalid_distance_codes (e.g., &lt;=0, NaN, &gt;max_range).
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>

                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--12</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>SA_ControlLoopHook</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Registration with Scheduler as stage 1 of the control loop:
                                - SA_Update() to be called once per loop before mapping and mission control.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>SA_ControlLoopTick</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Periodic control-loop tick defining sensor sampling time; ensures sampling frequency equals control loop frequency T.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>

                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--1</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>SA_ValidSensorsAvailable</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Boolean flag that becomes true once at least one valid ultrasonic and valid IR reading (both left and right flags) have been successfully acquired since mission start.
                                Stays true for the rest of mission.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>SA_InitCompleted</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Initialization complete flag used to start sensor sampling only after basic initialization is done, preventing the use of uninitialized hardware.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
            </ConnectedComponents>
            <Execution>
                - On each SA_ControlLoopTick:
                  1) If InitCompleted is false: skip sampling and keep all outputs invalid.
                  2) If sampling_rate_hz equals control loop frequency:
                     - Call ultrasonic_get_distance once.
                     - Call infrared_get_dsl_status and infrared_get_dsr_status once.
                  3) Validate readings:
                     - If distance is negative, NaN, or outside supported range, mark ultrasonic reading invalid and optionally substitute a large safe default (e.g., max_range_cm) for collision checks.
                     - Interpret IR statuses as binary flags; treat out-of-range values as "no obstacle" or invalid per configuration.
                  4) Insert new readings into temporal filter window per sensor.
                  5) Compute filtered values:
                     - For ultrasonic: median or average of valid samples in the window; if none valid, mark output valid=false.
                     - For IR: majority or debounced reading over last window_size samples for each side.
                  6) Update normalized output structures and timestamp.
                  7) Update ValidSensorsAvailable to true once a cycle occurs where both ultrasonic.valid and IR data are valid.
            </Execution>
            <Timing>
                - Sensor sampling and filtering is executed directly in the control loop; period T chosen such that 10 Hz ≤ 1/T ≤ 50 Hz.
                - Sampling jitter must be bounded per configuration; Scheduler ensures stable sampling period.
                - Filter window size and sampling rate trade off responsiveness vs smoothing. Default: 20 Hz, window size 3.
            </Timing>
            <Invariants>
                - At most one ultrasonic_get_distance and one infrared_get_xxx_status call per control loop cycle.
                - Normalized outputs are updated once per loop and remain unchanged between loops.
                - Invalid readings (e.g., negative distances) are never used directly for mapping or control decisions downstream.
                - sampling_rate_hz == control_loop_frequency_hz from Scheduler.
            </Invariants>
            <Failures>
                - Sensor permanent invalidity:
                  * If ultrasonic distance remains invalid for more than K consecutive cycles (configurable), mark a degraded mode flag (handled in Additional Data) for higher-level modules to reduce speed or rely more on IR-based wall detection.
                - Filter saturation:
                  * If filter window contains conflicting IR readings (oscillating) beyond hysteresis thresholds, treat them as no obstacle until stabilized (prevents spurious walls/maneuvers).
            </Failures>
            <DerivedFrom>
                LL--RELIAB--1.2.1
                LL--INTERF--1.1.1
                LL--INTERF--1.1.2
                LL--INTERF--2.1.1
                LL--INTERF--3.1.1
                LL--SCHED--1.1.1
                LL--INIT--1.1.1
            </DerivedFrom>
        </Component>

        <Component>
            <ID>CMP--4</ID>
            <Name>Wall Detection and Proximity Evaluation</Name>
            <Purpose>
                Interpret filtered ultrasonic and IR measurements as front and side walls and evaluate collision risk and clearance based on uncertainty and robot footprint.

                Responsibilities:
                - Detect front walls using ultrasonic distance and the ultrasonic uncertainty model versus expected robot-center-to-wall distance.
                - Detect side walls using IR obstacle flags when robot pose is aligned to maze axes within a given angular tolerance.
                - Apply configurable thresholds and hysteresis to ultrasonic data to avoid flip-flopping between wall and free classifications.
                - Compute wall proximity assessments for collision avoidance, including emergency-stop threshold checks and maintaining minimum clearance margin M.
                - Transform sensor detections into maze-referenced wall positions and lateral distances, accounting for IR orientation and effective range.
            </Purpose>
            <ConnectedComponents>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--3</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>WD_SensorConsumption</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Indicates that Wall Detection reads SA_NormalizedUltrasonic and SA_NormalizedIR each cycle; no additional payload.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>SA_NormalizedUltrasonic</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Filtered ultrasonic measurement (distance_cm, valid, timestamp).
                                Used for wall presence and proximity evaluation; uncertainty ±12 cm applied according to Ultrasonic Uncertainty Model.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>SA_NormalizedIR</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Filtered IR obstacle flags (left_flag, right_flag, timestamp) used for side wall detections.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>

                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--10</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>WD_PoseUsage</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Wall Detection uses current pose (cell index, heading, continuous orientation) to compute:
                                - expected center-to-wall distance for current cell (front, left, right),
                                - alignment error vs maze axes.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>WD_CurrentPoseDetailed</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Pose structure including:
                                - cell index (row, col),
                                - discrete heading for maze axes alignment,
                                - continuous orientation (float degrees or radians) to check angle tolerance ≤ 10° for side wall detection.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>

                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--5</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>WD_WallObservations</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Wall observation messages for mapping:
                                - type: {FRONT_WALL, LEFT_WALL, RIGHT_WALL, FRONT_FREE, SIDE_FREE},
                                - cell (row, col),
                                - wall_direction: {NORTH, SOUTH, EAST, WEST},
                                - confidence: value based on thresholds and hysteresis,
                                - proximity_distance_cm: estimated true distance to wall surface.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>WD_MapWallExpectations</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Current classification and geometric parameters of walls around current cell from Grid Map:
                                - present/absent/unknown for each direction,
                                - min/max allowed distances accounting for wall thickness and robot radius.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>

                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--2</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>WD_CollisionRiskAssessment</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Computed proximity relative to minimum clearance M and emergency-stop distance:
                                - min_distance_ahead_cm (including uncertainty),
                                - min_lateral_clearance_cm,
                                - clearance_violation (bool),
                                - emergency_stop_required (bool).
                                Consumed by Motion Control for avoidance maneuvers and emergency stops.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>WD_ClearanceConfig</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Configuration parameters:
                                - minimum_clearance_margin_M_cm (&gt;0),
                                - emergency_distance_threshold_cm,
                                - ultrasonic_uncertainty_cm (≥12),
                                - IR_effective_range_cm (≈4),
                                - IR_mount_angle_deg (≈25).
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
            </ConnectedComponents>
            <Execution>
                - Executed once per control loop after Sensor Abstraction and Pose Estimation and before Mapping and Motion Control.
                - For front wall detection (using ultrasonic):
                  1) Compute expected center-to-wall distance for the current cell in the heading direction:
                     - d_expected = (cell_size_cm / 2) - robot_radius_cm - wall_thickness_cm/2.
                  2) Given measured distance d_meas:
                     - Construct measurement interval [d_meas - 12, d_meas + 12] cm.
                  3) If interval intersects [d_expected - tolerance, d_expected + tolerance]:
                     - Interpret as front wall PRESENT for the wall at cell boundary in front of current cell, considering thresholds/hysteresis.
                  4) If interval is entirely greater than d_expected + margin:
                     - Interpret as FRONT_FREE up to at least one cell length for mapping and avoidance.
                  5) Apply hysteresis thresholds:
                     - Use two thresholds distance_near and distance_far to avoid rapid toggling between wall and free when readings bounce around boundary values.
                - For side wall detection (using IR):
                  1) Check continuous orientation: if |heading_error| ≤ angular_tolerance_deg (≤10° configurable, default 5°-10°):
                     - If left_flag == true, infer LEFT_WALL along left side of current cell at IR_effective_range corrected for mount angle and robot radius.
                     - If right_flag == true, infer RIGHT_WALL analogously.
                  2) If flags false and previously detected wall with high confidence, keep classification unchanged unless contradicted per consistency checks.
                  3) Transform detection into maze reference frame:
                     - Use IR_effective_range (≈4 cm) and IR_mount_angle (≈25°) to back-project detection onto the cell side boundary and store as PRESENT/ABSENT candidate.
                - Collision and clearance evaluation:
                  1) For forward direction:
                     - Compute estimated distance to nearest obstacle along path, using both ultrasonic and map-based expected walls.
                     - Subtract ultrasonic_uncertainty to obtain conservative min_distance.
                  2) Compare min_distance with:
                     - minimum_clearance_margin_M_cm + robot_radius_cm: set clearance_violation if violated even at 0 speed.
                     - emergency_distance_threshold_cm matched to current speed: set emergency_stop_required if min_distance &lt; threshold.
                  3) For side directions:
                     - Estimate lateral clearance using IR and map data; set clearance_violation if below M.
            </Execution>
            <Timing>
                - Evaluated once per control loop with same period T as sensor sampling and control loop.
                - Hysteresis behavior is time-discrete, dependent on number of cycles of consistent readings.
                - Wall classification decisions from a single sample are delayed until filter/hysteresis conditions are satisfied, typically across 2-3 cycles, to prevent flip-flopping.
            </Timing>
            <Invariants>
                - Front wall detection must consider the ultrasonic uncertainty interval of at least ±12 cm around measured value.
                - Side wall detection is only used for map updates if |heading_error| ≤ configured angular_tolerance_deg ≤ 10°.
                - Once a wall is confirmed and propagated to mapping, subsequent sensor readings cannot directly change classification from PRESENT to ABSENT or vice versa; such changes must be routed through consistency checks.
                - Clearance margin M is always applied relative to robot radius + wall positions.
            </Invariants>
            <Failures>
                - Ambiguous readings:
                  * When repeated inconsistent ultrasonic/IR data produce overlapping but contradictory interpretations, Wall Detection marks observations with low confidence and refrains from updating map until Consistency Check module resolves.
                - Sensor blind zone:
                  * If measured front distance is smaller than physical minimum (e.g., due to echo or saturation), treat as immediate obstacle; set emergency_stop_required, but record the map update only with lower confidence, leaving final decision to grid map plus consistency checks.
            </Failures>
            <DerivedFrom>
                LL--MAP--1.2.1
                LL--MAP--1.2.2
                LL--MAP--1.2.3
                LL--MAP--1.2.4
                LL--RELIAB--1.1.1
                LL--RELIAB--1.1.2
                LL--RELIAB--1.2.1
                LL--INTERF--2.3.1
                LL--INTERF--3.3.1
                LL--INTERF--3.4.1
                LL--HARDWARE--1.1.1
                LL--ENV--1.2.1
                LL--ENV--1.3.1
            </DerivedFrom>
        </Component>

        <Component>
            <ID>CMP--5</ID>
            <Name>Grid Map and Frontier Management</Name>
            <Purpose>
                Maintain the 4×8 grid map of maze cells and inter-cell wall segments; provide query, update, and notification interfaces; implement frontier generation, map completeness evaluation, and cell/wall classification policies.

                Responsibilities:
                - Represent cells with enumeration {UNKNOWN, FREE, BLOCKED} and walls with {UNKNOWN, PRESENT, ABSENT}.
                - Initialize all cells/walls to UNKNOWN at startup and designate the start cell as FREE with stored coordinates.
                - Update cells and walls based on wall detection observations and pose information, enforcing static map assumptions (no reversion or contradicted transitions).
                - Mark traversed cells as FREE if entered without collision, and mark neighboring cells BLOCKED if a separating wall is PRESENT.
                - Define and compute map completeness criterion; provide boolean map_complete to other modules.
                - Provide grid map access interface (query/update functions) and notification mechanism when classifications change.
                - Implement frontier generation: identify all UNKNOWN cells that are 4-neighbors of at least one FREE cell.
            </Purpose>
            <ConnectedComponents>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--4</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>GM_WallClassificationUpdates</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Requests to update wall segments based on wall observations:
                                - cell (row, col),
                                - wall_direction,
                                - new_state candidate {PRESENT, ABSENT},
                                - observation_confidence.
                                Grid Map applies static map rules and consistency checks before committing.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>GM_CellTraversalUpdates</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Requests to update cell classification when robot traverses cells:
                                - from_cell (row, col),
                                - to_cell (row, col),
                                - collision_detected_on_entry_face (bool).
                                Used to mark new cells as FREE on successful traversal without collision.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>WD_WallObservations</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Wall observations from Wall Detection with direction and confidence; used to update internal wall segments.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>

                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--10</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>GM_CurrentCellForMapping</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Grid Map requests current cell index from Pose Estimation when updating traversals and wall indices.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>GM_CellEntryNotification</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Notification from Pose Estimation for each crossing from one cell center to adjacent cell center:
                                - previous_cell (row, col),
                                - new_cell (row, col),
                                - heading_direction.
                                Used to mark new_cell as FREE (if no collision) and to index entry walls.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>

                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--6</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>GM_MapAccessInterface</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Logical interface providing:
                                - QueryCell(row, col) → {UNKNOWN, FREE, BLOCKED},
                                - QueryWall(row, col, direction) → {UNKNOWN, PRESENT, ABSENT},
                                - UpdateCell(row, col, new_state),
                                - UpdateWall(row, col, direction, new_state),
                                - SubscribeOnClassificationChange(callback/observer).
                                Internally realized as function calls; documented as a signal interface here.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>GM_MapChangeNotification</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Event-style notification:
                                - changed_type: {CELL, WALL},
                                - indices: (row,col,direction),
                                - old_state,
                                - new_state.
                                Sent to subscribers (Path Planner, Frontier Generator, Exploration Status) when a classification changes.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>GM_PathPlannerRequestsWithMap</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Path Planner requests map queries through the map access interface; includes needed cells/walls along search frontier.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>

                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--1</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>GM_MapCompletenessBoolean</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Boolean flag map_complete that is true if no cell and no inter-cell wall segment remain UNKNOWN.
                                Provided to Mission Control via Exploration Status module.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>GM_FrontierTargets</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Set/list of frontier cells computed for exploration:
                                - frontier_cells: array of (row, col) satisfying:
                                  * cell.state == UNKNOWN,
                                  * exists at least one of its 4-neighbors with state FREE.
                                Computed on request by Mission Control for exploration.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>GM_FrontierRequest</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Request from Mission Control or Planner to (re)compute current frontier set, or to provide next best frontier for exploration target selection.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>

                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--11</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>GM_MapChangeEventsForExplorationStatus</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Simplified notification:
                                - map_complete (bool),
                                - last_change_timestamp.
                                Used by Exploration Status to decide when to raise EXPLORATION_COMPLETED event.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>GM_ExplorationPhaseHint</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Phase information (ACTIVE, PAUSED, etc.) to control whether frontier generation and completeness checks are performed (primarily during EXPLORE).
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>

                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--9</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>GM_GoalRegionCandidates</Name>
                            <Description>
                                List of candidate 2×2 FREE regions once exploration completes:
                                - each candidate: four cell coordinates, plus connectivity/reachable flag.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>GM_ExplorationCompletedSignal</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Notification from Exploration Status that map is complete and exploration phase is over, used to trigger goal region identification.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
            </ConnectedComponents>
            <Execution>
                - Initialization:
                  1) At system startup (after InitCompleted but before EXPLORE):
                     - Allocate grid map arrays:
                       * cells[4][8] with initial state UNKNOWN,
                       * walls for vertical and horizontal boundaries as per Inter-Cell Wall Indexing, all UNKNOWN.
                     - Designate start cell coordinate (e.g., (row=0, col=0) per Grid Coordinate System).
                     - Set cells[start_cell] = FREE and store StartCellCoordinate for future use.
                - On each control loop:
                  1) On GM_CellEntryNotification from Pose:
                     - Mark new_cell as FREE if its state is UNKNOWN and no collision_on_entry_face was reported.
                     - For each traversed wall between previous_cell and new_cell:
                       * Ensure that if wall is PRESENT, traversal does not mark new_cell FREE (contradiction; rely on Consistency Checks).
                  2) On WD_WallObservations:
                     - For each observation (cell, direction, candidate_state):
                       * If wall is UNKNOWN:
                          - Update to PRESENT or ABSENT according to candidate_state, subject to consistency checks.
                       * If wall is PRESENT/ABSENT and candidate suggests UNKNOWN or opposite state:
                          - Do not change directly; send to Consistency Checks module for possible re-evaluation (via Additional Data configuration).
                     - For each wall marked PRESENT between cell A and neighbor B:
                       * If neighbor cell is UNKNOWN, set neighbor state to BLOCKED (Blocked Cell Inference).
                  3) Map completeness:
                     - Maintain counters of UNKNOWN cells and walls, updated on each UpdateCell/UpdateWall.
                     - map_complete = (num_unknown_cells == 0) AND (num_unknown_walls == 0).
                     - On transition map_complete false→true: send MapCompletenessBoolean change to Exploration Status/Mission Control.
                  4) Frontier generation:
                     - On explicit GM_FrontierRequest or when cells change from UNKNOWN to FREE/BLOCKED:
                       * Recompute or incrementally update frontier list as all cells with:
                         cell.state == UNKNOWN AND exists 4-neighbor with cell.state == FREE.
                     - Keep frontier list current during EXPLORE.
                - Grid Map Access Interface:
                  - Query and update calls are pure functions and procedures executed inside control loop, ensuring single-threaded access.
            </Execution>
            <Timing>
                - All map queries/updates/notifications occur inside the periodic control loop (same context as mapping and planning).
                - Frontier generation may be recomputed in full or incremental mode once per relevant map update to keep computation within real-time bounds; given 4×8 map, full recomputation every update is acceptable.
                - Map completeness check is O(1) due to maintained counters, updated each time a cell or wall transitions from UNKNOWN.
            </Timing>
            <Invariants>
                - Each cell is always in exactly one state ∈ {UNKNOWN, FREE, BLOCKED}.
                - Allowed cell transitions within mission:
                  * UNKNOWN → FREE,
                  * UNKNOWN → BLOCKED.
                  No other transitions allowed.
                - Each wall segment is in exactly one state ∈ {UNKNOWN, PRESENT, ABSENT}.
                - Allowed wall transitions within mission:
                  * UNKNOWN → PRESENT,
                  * UNKNOWN → ABSENT.
                  No other transitions allowed.
                - Once map_complete is true, it remains true for the remainder of the mission.
                - StartCellCoordinate remains fixed for entire mission and cell[start] == FREE.
            </Invariants>
            <Failures>
                - Inconsistent update attempts:
                  * If an update attempts to set a cell from FREE/BLOCKED back to UNKNOWN or to the other non-UNKNOWN state directly, Grid Map rejects the update, logs an error via diagnostics (Additional Data), and optionally increments an error counter.
                - External indexing error:
                  * If a query or update request uses out-of-range row/column indices, operation is rejected and error is logged; map is not altered.
            </Failures>
