        <Component>
            <ID>CMP--6</ID>
            <Name>Path Planner</Name>
            <Purpose>
                Implement cell-based path planning (Dijkstra/A*) over the 4×8 grid map; handle path optimality based on traversal cost model, replanning, handling of goal regions, time-aware planning, and planning failure reporting.

                Responsibilities:
                - Maintain traversal cost model with separate costs for straight moves and turns.
                - Compute optimal paths from a start cell to:
                  * single target cell (frontier or start cell),
                  * any cell in a 2×2 goal region, minimizing traversal cost.
                - Implement Dijkstra or A* over FREE cells, using 4-connected adjacency and disallowing transitions across PRESENT walls.
                - Support time-aware planning: reject frontier targets whose estimated travel time exceeds remaining exploration time.
                - Recompute paths when map changes invalidate current paths (via Map Change Notifications).
                - Report planning failure when no path exists.
            </Purpose>
            <ConnectedComponents>
