    <StateMachines version="1">
        <StateMachine>
            <ID>FSM--1</ID>
            <OfComponent>CMP--1</OfComponent>
            <States>
                <State>
                    <Name>IDLE</Name>
                    <StateAction>
                        - Maintain robot stopped (by ensuring Motion Control is in STOP mode).
                        - Monitor INIT_COMPLETED flag and ValidSensorsAvailable from Sensor Abstraction.
                        - Do not request paths or move.
                    </StateAction>
                </State>
                <State>
                    <Name>EXPLORE</Name>
                    <StateAction>
                        - Periodically (each control loop or on completion of previous path segment):
                          1) Request frontier cell set from Grid Map’s Frontier Generator.
                          2) Evaluate and rank frontier cells using Exploration Target Selection Heuristic and Time-Aware Planning (estimated travel-time vs remaining_exploration_time_ms).
                          3) Select best feasible frontier as navigation target.
                          4) Invoke Path Planner (request_type=EXPLORE_TARGET) to compute path from current cell to selected frontier.
                          5) On success: command Motion Control to FOLLOW_PATH at EXPLORATION_SPEED.
                        - Continuously monitor:
                          * EXPLORATION_COMPLETED and EXPLORATION_TIMEOUT events from Exploration Status.
                          * PathExecutionStatus, including goal_reached or aborted.
                    </StateAction>
                </State>
                <State>
                    <Name>RETURN_TO_START</Name>
                    <StateAction>
                        - Invoke Return-To-Start service:
                          * Request path from current cell to StartCellCoordinate (Path Planner request_type=RETURN_TO_START).
                        - On path success: command Motion Control to FOLLOW_PATH at EXPLORATION_SPEED (or safe speed).
                        - Monitor:
                          * PathExecutionStatus.goal_reached for arrival at start.
                          * Planning failures or aborts to decide mission completion with failure.
                    </StateAction>
                </State>
                <State>
                    <Name>SECOND_RUN</Name>
                    <StateAction>
                        - When entry condition satisfied (robot at start cell, exploration complete):
                          1) Obtain selected goal region from Goal Region Identification.
                          2) Request fastest path via Path Planner (request_type=SECOND_RUN) using configured cost model for physical travel time.
                          3) On success: command Motion Control to FOLLOW_PATH at SECOND_RUN_SPEED.
                          4) Set SecondRunStatusOut = RUNNING.
                        - Monitor:
                          * PathExecutionStatus.second_run_goal_reached; on success, set SecondRunStatusOut = SUCCESS.
                          * aborts or collisions; on failure, set SecondRunStatusOut = FAILURE.
                    </StateAction>
                </State>
                <State>
                    <Name>COMPLETED</Name>
                    <StateAction>
                        - Ensure Motion Control is in STOP mode; do not issue new FOLLOW_PATH commands.
                        - Maintain final SecondRunStatusOut value (SUCCESS or FAILURE).
                        - Provide final mission outcome for external reporting; no further mission activity until reset.
                    </StateAction>
                </State>
            </States>
            <Transitions>
                <Transition>
                    <From>IDLE</From>
                    <To>EXPLORE</To>
                    <Trigger>
                        - INIT_COMPLETED flag set by Initialization Module AND ValidSensorsAvailable == true (from Sensor Abstraction) evaluated in the control loop.
                    </Trigger>
                    <Guard>
                        - No existing mission in progress (MC state currently IDLE).
                    </Guard>
                    <TransitionAction>
                        - Record exploration_start_time via Exploration Status.
                        - Ensure map is in initial state with start cell FREE.
                    </TransitionAction>
                </Transition>

                <Transition>
                    <From>EXPLORE</From>
                    <To>RETURN_TO_START</To>
                    <Trigger>
                        - Receipt of either:
                          * EXPLORATION_COMPLETED event (map_complete == true), OR
                          * EXPLORATION_TIMEOUT event (elapsed exploration time ≥ 5 minutes).
                    </Trigger>
                    <Guard>
                        - Path execution for current frontier exploration is either idle, completed, or can be safely stopped.
                    </Guard>
                    <TransitionAction>
                        - Command Motion Control to STOP current exploration motion safely.
                        - Invoke Return-To-Start service to compute path to start cell.
                    </TransitionAction>
                </Transition>

                <Transition>
                    <From>RETURN_TO_START</From>
                    <To>SECOND_RUN</To>
                    <Trigger>
                        - PathExecutionStatus.goal_reached == true for path to start cell, AND
                        - Exploration was declared complete by Exploration Status (EXPLORATION_COMPLETED occurred at some point; timeout alone is not sufficient for SECOND_RUN).
                    </Trigger>
                    <Guard>
                        - No outstanding planning failure for return path.
                    </Guard>
                    <TransitionAction>
                        - Set SecondRunStatusOut = NOT_STARTED (or reset from any previous value).
                        - Invoke Second-Run Initialization logic (LL--RUN--1.2.1).
                    </TransitionAction>
                </Transition>

                <Transition>
                    <From>RETURN_TO_START</From>
                    <To>COMPLETED</To>
                    <Trigger>
                        - Return-To-Start planning failure signaled (PathPlannerResult.status == FAILURE_NO_PATH) OR
                        - PathExecutionStatus.aborted == true and replanning failed.
                    </Trigger>
                    <Guard>
                        - Only one failure-handling attempt has already been made.
                    </Guard>
                    <TransitionAction>
                        - Set SecondRunStatusOut = FAILURE.
                        - Command Motion Control to STOP.
                    </TransitionAction>
                </Transition>

                <Transition>
                    <From>SECOND_RUN</From>
                    <To>COMPLETED</To>
                    <Trigger>
                        - Either:
                          * PathExecutionStatus.second_run_goal_reached == true, OR
                          * PathExecutionStatus.aborted == true, OR
                          * Planning failure for fastest path (FAILURE_NO_PATH).
                    </Trigger>
                    <Guard>
                        - For success branch: no collision or emergency stop occurred during SECOND_RUN.
                    </Guard>
                    <TransitionAction>
                        - If success: set SecondRunStatusOut = SUCCESS.
                        - If failure: set SecondRunStatusOut = FAILURE.
                        - Command Motion Control to STOP.
                    </TransitionAction>
                </Transition>
            </Transitions>
