<Findings version="1" source="Design" source_version="1">
    <Finding ID="Design--1--1">
        <ItemID>CMP--12</ItemID>
        <Severity>Major</Severity>
        <Description>
            In the Scheduler and Control Loop component, the &lt;ConnectedComponent&gt; for CMP--2 (Motion Control) incorrectly defines the same signal name &quot;MC_ControlLoopHook&quot; under both &lt;Transmit&gt; and &lt;Receive&gt;:
            - At the component level, CMP--2 already defines a &quot;MC_ControlLoopHook&quot; transmit/receive pair with CMP--12.
            - In CMP--12, for the Motion Control connection, the &lt;Transmit&gt; signal is named &quot;Sched_TickToMCtrl&quot;, but the &lt;Receive&gt; signal is incorrectly named &quot;MC_ControlLoopHook&quot; instead of &quot;Sched_TickToMCtrlHook&quot; or similar, and it duplicates the scheduler’s reception name used in the CMP--1 connection.
            This creates an inconsistent and ambiguous naming of control-loop registration/tick signals between scheduler and modules and can lead to confusion or misinterpretation of which module is registering which hook. It also breaks symmetry with other modules, where the pattern is consistently Sched_TickToX / X_ControlLoopHook.
        </Description>
        <Solution>
            Align the signal names for the Scheduler–Motion Control connection with the established pattern and remove the duplicate/incorrect name:
            - In CMP--12, under the &lt;ConnectedComponent&gt; with &lt;Identifier&gt;CMP--2&lt;/Identifier&gt;:
              * Keep the &lt;Transmit&gt; signal as:
                &lt;Name&gt;Sched_TickToMCtrl&lt;/Name&gt;
              * Change the &lt;Receive&gt; signal name from:
                &lt;Name&gt;MC_ControlLoopHook&lt;/Name&gt;
                to something consistent like:
                &lt;Name&gt;MCtrl_ControlLoopHook&lt;/Name&gt;
                or
                &lt;Name&gt;Sched_TickToMCtrlHook&lt;/Name&gt;
            - Alternatively, if the intention is that all modules register via &quot;X_ControlLoopHook&quot; and the scheduler only has *receive* signals, then:
              * In CMP--12, rename all &lt;Receive&gt; signal names to be unique per module (e.g., SA_ControlLoopHook, PE_ControlLoopHook, WD_ControlLoopHook, GM_ControlLoopHook, MC_ControlLoopHook, etc.) and ensure they match what each module transmits.
              * In the CMP--2 component’s &lt;ConnectedComponent&gt; for CMP--12, ensure its &lt;Transmit&gt; signal name exactly matches the CMP--12 &lt;Receive&gt; signal name (e.g., MC_ControlLoopHook), and its &lt;Receive&gt; matches Sched_TickToMCtrl.
            The key is to maintain a one-to-one, unambiguous mapping of registration/tick pairs without reusing signal names across different logical directions or modules.
        </Solution>
        <RollbackPhase>Design</RollbackPhase>
    </Finding>
</Findings> 

