        </Component>
    </Components>

    <StateMachines version="1">
        <StateMachine>
            <ID>FSM--1</ID>
            <OfComponent>CMP--1</OfComponent>
            <States>
                <State>
                    <Name>IDLE</Name>
                    <StateAction>
                        - Keep motors stopped (no MC_MotionCommand).
                        - Monitor INIT_COMPLETED and SensorAvailabilityStatus flags.
                        - Initialize exploration-related timers and flags upon future exit.
                    </StateAction>
                </State>
                <State>
                    <Name>EXPLORE</Name>
                    <StateAction>
                        - Periodically request frontier targets from CMP--2.
                        - Send MC_PathPlanningRequest to CMP--4 for selected frontier cell.
                        - If path available, issue MC_MotionCommand in exploration speed profile to CMP--8.
                        - Monitor ExplorationEvents and pose to detect exploration completion/timeout.
                    </StateAction>
                </State>
                <State>
                    <Name>RETURN_TO_START</Name>
                    <StateAction>
                        - Invoke return-to-start service: request path from current cell to start cell.
                        - Command motion control to execute return path.
                        - Monitor ReturnToStartStatus for completion or failure.
                    </StateAction>
                </State>
                <State>
                    <Name>SECOND_RUN</Name>
                    <StateAction>
                        - Request fastest path from start cell to selected goal region with time-optimized traversal cost.
                        - Command motion control to execute path with higher speed profile respecting safety.
                        - Monitor second run execution status to derive success/failure.
                    </StateAction>
                </State>
                <State>
                    <Name>COMPLETED</Name>
                    <StateAction>
                        - Cease issuing new MC_MotionCommand (motors left stopped by motion control).
                        - Maintain final second-run status in MC_SecondRunStatusOutput for external reporting.
                    </StateAction>
                </State>
            </States>
            <Transitions>
                <Transition>
                    <From>IDLE</From>
                    <To>EXPLORE</To>
                    <Trigger>
                        INIT_COMPLETED indication present AND SensorAvailabilityStatus is true, both sampled within control loop.
                    </Trigger>
                    <Guard>
                        - No critical errors in initialization.
                        - Map initialized with start cell set to FREE.
                    </Guard>
                    <TransitionAction>
                        - Reset exploration timers and elapsed time counters.
                        - Initialize exploration modules (frontier generation, exploration-status).
                    </TransitionAction>
                </Transition>
                <Transition>
                    <From>EXPLORE</From>
                    <To>RETURN_TO_START</To>
                    <Trigger>
                        - Receipt of EXPLORATION_COMPLETED event OR
                        - Receipt of EXPLORATION_TIMEOUT event from exploration-status module, whichever occurs first.
                    </Trigger>
                    <Guard>
                        - Current motion commands are safe to stop or replan.
                    </Guard>
                    <TransitionAction>
                        - Stop issuing further frontier requests.
                        - Issue return-to-start path planning request from current cell to start cell.
                        - Set internal reason code (COMPLETED or TIMEOUT).
                    </TransitionAction>
                </Transition>
                <Transition>
                    <From>RETURN_TO_START</From>
                    <To>SECOND_RUN</To>
                    <Trigger>
                        - ReturnToStartStatus indicates REACHED_START.
                        - Exploration previously declared complete (EXPLORATION_COMPLETED event had occurred; TIMEOUT alone may still allow second run if map sufficient).
                    </Trigger>
                    <Guard>
                        - Robot pose at start cell (verified by pose estimate and possibly small tolerance).
                        - Start cell is FREE in map.
                    </Guard>
                    <TransitionAction>
                        - Request goal region identification/selection if not already done.
                        - Request fastest path plan (SECOND_RUN mode).
                        - Initialize MC_SecondRunStatusOutput to RUNNING.
                    </TransitionAction>
                </Transition>
                <Transition>
                    <From>RETURN_TO_START</From>
                    <To>COMPLETED</To>
                    <Trigger>
                        ReturnToStartStatus indicates PLANNING_FAILURE or ABORTED_COLLISION and no alternative route available.
                    </Trigger>
                    <Guard>
                        - Policy: mission ends if robot cannot return safely.
                    </Guard>
                    <TransitionAction>
                        - Set MC_SecondRunStatusOutput to FAILURE.
                        - Ensure motion commands are stopped.
                    </TransitionAction>
                </Transition>
                <Transition>
                    <From>SECOND_RUN</From>
                    <To>COMPLETED</To>
                    <Trigger>
                        - SecondRunExecutionStatus == SUCCESS_REACHED_GOAL OR
                        - SecondRunExecutionStatus == FAILURE_COLLISION OR
                        - Planning failure for fastest path.
                    </Trigger>
                    <Guard>
                        None beyond trigger; any terminal status ends mission.
                    </Guard>
                    <TransitionAction>
                        - Latch MC_SecondRunStatusOutput to SUCCESS or FAILURE depending on reported status.
                        - Stop issuing path execution commands to motion control.
                    </TransitionAction>
                </Transition>
            </Transitions>
            <DerivedFrom>
                LL--MAP--1.1.1 LL--MAP--1.1.2 LL--MAP--1.1.3 LL--MAP--1.1.4
                LL--MAP--1.5.1 LL--MAP--1.5.2
                LL--RUN--1.1.1 LL--RUN--1.1.2
                LL--RUN--1.2.1 LL--RUN--1.2.2 LL--RUN--1.2.3 LL--RUN--1.2.4 LL--RUN--1.2.5
                LL--EVENT--1.1.1 LL--INIT--1.1.1 LL--SCHED--1.1.1
            </DerivedFrom>
        </StateMachine>
    </StateMachines>

    <AdditionalData version="1">
        <Data>
            <ID>DAT--1</ID>
            <Content>
                Grid Map Data Structures:
                - Define:
                  enum CellState { CELL_UNKNOWN = 0, CELL_FREE = 1, CELL_BLOCKED = 2 };
                  enum WallState { WALL_UNKNOWN = 0, WALL_PRESENT = 1, WALL_ABSENT = 2 };
                - Cell storage:
                  CellState cells[4][8];
                - Wall storage:
                  - Horizontal walls between (row, col) and (row+1, col):
                    WallState hWalls[3][8];
                  - Vertical walls between (row, col) and (row, col+1):
                    WallState vWalls[4][7];
                - Coordinate convention (example):
                  - Row 0, Col 0 is start cell at bottom-left or a specified corner, as per HL environment.
                  All modules must consistently use this indexing.
            </Content>
            <DerivedFrom>
                LL--MAP--1.3.1 LL--MAP--1.4.1 LL--MAP--1.4.2 LL--ENV--1.1.1 LL--ENV--1.4.1
            </DerivedFrom>
        </Data>

        <Data>
            <ID>DAT--2</ID>
            <Content>
                Traversal Cost Model Parameters:
                - Define cost units such that:
                  baseStraightCost = 1.0 per move between adjacent FREE cells with no turn.
                  turnPenalty = configurable &gt;= 0 for turns between edges (e.g., 0.5).
                - Exploration profile:
                  - Emphasize information gain while maintaining reasonable path length; keep baseStraightCost small, turnPenalty modest.
                - Second-run profile:
                  - Set parameters corresponding to estimated travel time:
                    costPerStraightCell = cellLength / nominalSpeed.
                    costPerTurn = extra time to decelerate, turn, accelerate.
                - Cost computation:
                  For each path:
                    TotalCost = sum(edgeCosts) where edgeCost = baseStraightCost (+turnPenalty when heading changes).
            </Content>
            <DerivedFrom>
                LL--PLAN--1.1.2 LL--MAP--1.1.5 LL--RUN--1.2.2 LL--ENV--3.1.2
            </DerivedFrom>
        </Data>

        <Data>
            <ID>DAT--3</ID>
            <Content>
                Time-Aware Planning and Nominal Cell Traversal Duration:
                - Configuration parameter:
                  uint32_t nominalCellTraversalMs; // default derived from measured robot speed at exploration speed.
                - Remaining exploration time:
                  remainingTimeMs = max(0, explorationTimeLimitMs - elapsedExplorationMs).
                - Frontier feasibility test:
                  For candidate frontier at distance N_cells from current cell:
                    estTravelMs = N_cells * nominalCellTraversalMs;
                    estMappingOverheadMs = nominalCellTraversalMs; // simple fixed overhead.
                    If estTravelMs + estMappingOverheadMs &gt; remainingTimeMs, discard candidate.
            </Content>
            <DerivedFrom>
                LL--MAP--1.5.2 LL--MAP--1.5.3 LL--MAP--1.1.5
            </DerivedFrom>
        </Data>

        <Data>
            <ID>DAT--4</ID>
            <Content>
                Ultrasonic Uncertainty and Clearance Checks:
                - Ultrasonic measurement model:
                  Each distance reading d_cm is expanded to [d_cm - 12, d_cm + 12] cm interval.
                - Robot model:
                  Radius R = 5.5 cm.
                  Wall thickness ~1.6 cm.
                  Cell size L = 17.2 cm.
                - Expected center-to-wall distance for front wall when centered in cell:
                  approxDistance = L/2 + wallThickness/2 ≈ 8.6 + 0.8 = 9.4 cm (approximate; derived precisely in implementation).
                - Clearance margin M:
                  Configurable M &gt; 0 cm, e.g., 2–5 cm; planned trajectories ensure robot center stays at least R + M away from any wall boundary.
                - Emergency stop threshold:
                  Derived from maximum speed, stopping distance, and uncertainty interval; ensures robot can stop before wall even in worst-case measurement error.
            </Content>
            <DerivedFrom>
                LL--INTERF--2.3.1 LL--HARDWARE--1.1.1 LL--ENV--1.2.1 LL--ENV--1.3.1
                LL--RELIAB--1.1.1 LL--RELIAB--1.1.2 LL--MAP--1.2.1
            </DerivedFrom>
        </Data>

        <Data>
            <ID>DAT--5</ID>
            <Content>
                Sensor Filtering and Consistency Parameters:
                - Sampling frequency:
                  configurable in [10, 50] Hz; default 20 Hz.
                  controlLoopPeriod T = 1 / samplingFrequency.
                - Filter windows:
                  ultrasonicMovingAverageWindow = 3–5 samples.
                  IRmovingAverageOrDebounceWindow = 2–3 samples.
                - Consistency threshold N for changing map entries from FREE/ABSENT to BLOCKED/PRESENT:
                  integer N ∈ [2, 10], default 3.
                  Implementation: maintain counters per cell/wall; only change classification when N consecutive readings indicate a change.
            </Content>
            <DerivedFrom>
                LL--RELIAB--1.2.1 LL--RELIAB--1.2.2
            </DerivedFrom>
        </Data>

        <Data>
            <ID>DAT--6</ID>
            <Content>
                Motion Primitive Specification:
                - Straight move primitive:
                  Move from one cell center to adjacent in direction of current discrete heading.
                  Steps:
                  1) Compute distance to travel = cellLength (17.2 cm).
                  2) Compute required duration based on exploration or second-run speed (cm/s).
                  3) Execute repeated motor_set commands with equal left/right speeds for computed number of control loop cycles.
                - Turn in place primitive:
                  Rotate by ±90° or 180° to align with maze axis.
                  Use differential drive kinematics to determine wheel speeds and duration for desired angle based on robot geometry.
                - Arc turn primitive for avoidance:
                  Use left/right speeds with appropriate ratio to follow circular arc of radius &gt;= R + M to maintain clearance from walls.
            </Content>
            <DerivedFrom>
                LL--HARDWARE--2.1.2 LL--HARDWARE--2.1.1 LL--MAP--1.2.4 LL--ENV--1.2.1 LL--RELIAB--1.1.1
            </DerivedFrom>
        </Data>

        <Data>
            <ID>DAT--7</ID>
            <Content>
                Event Queue for Exploration and Mission Events:
                - Data structure:
                  Circular buffer of fixed size (e.g., 16 entries) storing:
                  struct Event { EventType type; uint32_t timestamp; EventPayload payload; };
                - Supported event types include:
                  EXPLORATION_COMPLETED, EXPLORATION_TIMEOUT, PATH_INVALIDATED, RETURN_COMPLETED, SECOND_RUN_COMPLETED.
                - Usage:
                  - Modules (e.g., exploration-status) enqueue events.
                  - Mission control dequeues and processes all available events each control loop.
            </Content>
            <DerivedFrom>
                LL--EVENT--1.1.1 LL--MAP--1.5.1 LL--RUN--1.1.1 LL--MAP--1.1.1
            </DerivedFrom>
        </Data>
    </AdditionalData>
</Design>
